The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, August 06, 2004 				 An evening for the Eves
																								It is a concept that has indeed travelled a long way since its birth in the US. Open Mike story sharing session is a rare opportunity for women to get together and share stories from their experiences as women in a largely male dominated society. That Takes Ovaries is the name of one such Open Mike story sharing session that will allow for women in the city to come together and regale in a feisty evening of estrogen powered tales ranging from the playful to the political. It is a unique occasion when one learns of ordinary women who have done everything from the extraordinary to the outrageous. In a span of close to two years, the city has played host to seven such sessions. And each session has been rewarding in that it has increased the level of awareness and confidence among the women folk in society. That Takes Ovaries will be conducted by Mira Kakkar of Thoughtshop Foundation and will be graced by Usha Uthup as the special quot;Ovarian quot; guest.																								Event: That Takes Ovaries, Open Mike Story Sharing Session																								When: Today; 5.30 pm - 7.30 pm																								Where: Crossword Book Store, 8 Elgin Road
